{"id":97,"date":"2017-05-12T14:51:07","date_gmt":"2017-05-12T14:51:07","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/auticure.techeezy.com\/?p=97"},"modified":"2025-07-23T13:27:52","modified_gmt":"2025-07-23T13:27:52","slug":"the-isolation-i-sometimes-feel-as-a-special-needs-parent","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/auticure.techeezy.com\/2017\/05\/12\/the-isolation-i-sometimes-feel-as-a-special-needs-parent\/","title":{"rendered":"The Isolation I Sometimes Feel as a Special Needs Parent"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>There are moments \u2014 quiet ones, in the middle of the night or after a long day \u2014 when I feel an invisible kind of loneliness. I love my child fiercely. I celebrate every tiny victory, fight for every service, and gladly walk a harder path to support their needs. But behind the strength I show the world, there are times when I feel deeply alone.<\/p>\n<p>Friends who once checked in have grown silent, unsure of what to say. Birthday party invites stopped arriving years ago. I scroll through social media and see pictures of \u201ctypical\u201d milestones \u2014 school plays, sleepovers, easy days \u2014 and a strange ache rises. Not jealousy. Just\u2026 distance. Like I\u2019m living in a parallel world where the rules are different and few can truly understand.<\/p>\n<p>The isolation isn\u2019t always physical. It\u2019s emotional. It\u2019s sitting at a parent-teacher meeting trying to explain your child\u2019s behavior again, knowing they\u2019re more than the checklist being used to define them. It\u2019s pretending to laugh when someone offers unsolicited advice \u2014 as if love alone could make everything easier. It\u2019s not being able to share your worries, because even the well-meaning people don\u2019t get it.<\/p>\n<p>Sometimes, I envy parents who can simply drop their child at school and trust that the day will go smoothly. My mornings are different \u2014 packed with preparation, with warnings, with plans B, C, and D in case a meltdown happens, or if something changes that my child can\u2019t handle. It\u2019s not just exhausting. It\u2019s isolating.<\/p>\n<p>But within that solitude, something else grows. A quiet strength. A kind of love that is both tender and fierce. And in time, I\u2019ve found glimmers of connection \u2014 other parents who walk this road too. We speak in shorthand, through tired smiles and knowing looks. With them, I don\u2019t have to explain. I don\u2019t have to be \u201cstrong.\u201d I just have to be real.<\/p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re reading this and feel that same quiet isolation \u2014 I see you. You\u2019re not alone, even when it feels that way. This path is hard, but it\u2019s also full of hidden beauty. And sometimes, simply knowing that someone else understands can be the bridge that carries us through the hardest days.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>There are moments \u2014 quiet ones, in the middle of the night or after a long day \u2014 when I feel an invisible kind of loneliness. I love my child fiercely. I celebrate every tiny victory, fight for every service, and gladly walk a harder path to support their needs. But behind the strength I show the world, there are&hellip;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":1806,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"pagelayer_contact_templates":[],"_pagelayer_content":"","footnotes":""},"categories":[16],"tags":[29,30],"class_list":["post-97","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-our-big-family","tag-funding","tag-tips"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/auticure.techeezy.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/97","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/auticure.techeezy.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/auticure.techeezy.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/auticure.techeezy.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/auticure.techeezy.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=97"}],"version-history":[{"count":1,"href":"https:\/\/auticure.techeezy.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/97\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":2033,"href":"https:\/\/auticure.techeezy.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/97\/revisions\/2033"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/auticure.techeezy.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/1806"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/auticure.techeezy.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=97"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/auticure.techeezy.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=97"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/auticure.techeezy.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=97"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}